{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/DedalusProject/dedalus/releases/72976110", "assets_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/DedalusProject/dedalus/releases/72976110/assets", "upload_url": "https://uploads.github.com/repos/DedalusProject/dedalus/releases/72976110/assets{?name,label}", "html_url": "https://github.com/DedalusProject/dedalus/releases/tag/v2.2207", "id": 72976110, "author": {"login": "kburns", "id": 1034150, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEwMzQxNTA=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1034150?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/kburns", "html_url": "https://github.com/kburns", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kburns/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kburns/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kburns/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kburns/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kburns/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kburns/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kburns/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kburns/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kburns/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "node_id": "RE_kwDOD8QN7c4EWYbu", "tag_name": "v2.2207", "target_commitish": "master", "name": "Dedalus v2.2207", "draft": false, "prerelease": false, "created_at": "2022-07-26T21:45:16Z", "published_at": "2022-07-27T15:30:45Z", "assets": [], "tarball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/DedalusProject/dedalus/tarball/v2.2207", "zipball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/DedalusProject/dedalus/zipball/v2.2207", "body": "**Note**: This is expected to be the last major v2 release. While we plan to continue issuing bugfixes and backporting major performance improvements and minor API additions from v3, we encourage new users to begin using v3.\r\n\r\nFeature additions:\r\n\r\n- Transposed LU factorizations for the direct solution of bordered problems without Dirichlet preconditioning. This enables the efficient use of e.g. integral boundary conditions (e1541b9ce1b968d8886889f68b513b0b00d2ba0c).\r\n- Interpolation can now be triggered by using a field/operator's `__call__` method, like `u(y='left')` (248922118c7bbbea77e5677de75efe588f258ea3).\r\n- Left eigenvectors now available with the sparse eigenvalue solver (ad264a476dd14909ff32661e536206a7aa229441).\r\n- Simplified stat logging has be backported from v3 (73981d803ce681f746b1a4562e6b82bd0d5c1c61).\r\n\r\nPerformance changes:\r\n\r\n- Improved sparse matrix applications and other performance improvements have been backported from v3 (36c8e14a40aa82f124097144b3670821fe0367f6).", "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/DedalusProject/dedalus/releases/72976110/reactions", "total_count": 2, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 2, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}}
{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/DedalusProject/dedalus/releases/31411602", "assets_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/DedalusProject/dedalus/releases/31411602/assets", "upload_url": "https://uploads.github.com/repos/DedalusProject/dedalus/releases/31411602/assets{?name,label}", "html_url": "https://github.com/DedalusProject/dedalus/releases/tag/v2.2006", "id": 31411602, "author": {"login": "kburns", "id": 1034150, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEwMzQxNTA=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1034150?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/kburns", "html_url": "https://github.com/kburns", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kburns/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kburns/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kburns/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kburns/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kburns/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kburns/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kburns/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kburns/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kburns/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "node_id": "MDc6UmVsZWFzZTMxNDExNjAy", "tag_name": "v2.2006", "target_commitish": "master", "name": "Dedalus v2.2006", "draft": false, "prerelease": false, "created_at": "2020-09-17T03:08:36Z", "published_at": "2020-09-16T16:58:19Z", "assets": [], "tarball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/DedalusProject/dedalus/tarball/v2.2006", "zipball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/DedalusProject/dedalus/zipball/v2.2006", "body": "Feature additions:\r\n- New `Legendre` polynomial basis (77d92e5253f2706ea0ebf0e9b99461bbfcc63dd4).\r\n- Problems now support variables marked as constant in the coupled dimension (see 1D Lane Emden example) (77d92e5253f2706ea0ebf0e9b99461bbfcc63dd4).\r\n- New methods for computing CFL times based on diffusive terms in conservative and non-conservative form (6e2cec29999db36e3cb5dfc9573a8c1db290b7ca).\r\n- Grid spacings are now available in the parsing namespace as e.g. `'sx'` for the `'x'` dimension (71219d1a1a67f51feb799aa8179d46765fdbfd38).\r\n- Number of tau rows removed per equation can now be specified with the `'tau'` keyword in `Problem.add_equation` (ce8c1317b13487012e4c518650de48b202fc8fa9).\r\n- New command-line options `get_config` and `get_examples` for copying the configuration file and example scripts (cc0373e742dcaa56c88db4d29a0b841a48b1d5c0).\r\n\r\nBehavior modifications:\r\n- Default value of `'ncc_cutoff'` changed from `1e-10` to `1e-6` to produce more banded NCC matrices (7efb88446b806a0dd0ffaec0d5d08fbd7689fb9c)\r\n- Default value of `'entry_cutoff`' changed from `0` to `1e-12` to prevent rounding errors from reducing matrix sparsity (7efb88446b806a0dd0ffaec0d5d08fbd7689fb9c).\r\n- Hermitian symmetry for real problems is now explicitly enforced every 100 iterations by default. This can be modified via the `'enforce_real_cadence'` keyword for IVP solvers (5b3be571679a73ae7e28d77af093c1ba61c0f4e3).\r\n\r\nPerformance changes:\r\n- Improved strategy for reducing the number of transforms when evaluating RHS terms (0ce1482b3516bcb4052b9babd029c191e04f2da1)."}
